.TH "nilfs_ioctl_do_get_suinfo" 9 "nilfs_ioctl_do_get_suinfo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_ioctl_do_get_suinfo \- callback method getting segment usage info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" nilfs_ioctl_do_get_suinfo
.BI "(struct the_nilfs *nilfs "  ","
.BI "__u64 *posp "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t nmembs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nilfs" 12
nilfs object
.IP "posp" 12
pointer on array of segment numbers
.IP "flags" 12
*not used*
.IP "buf" 12
buffer for storing suinfo array
.IP "size" 12
size in bytes of one suinfo item in array
.IP "nmembs" 12
count of segment numbers and suinfos in array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_ioctl_do_get_suinfo\fP function returns segment usage
info about requested segments. The NILFS_IOCTL_GET_SUINFO ioctl is used
in lssu, nilfs_resize utilities and by nilfs_cleanerd daemon.

Return value: count of nilfs_suinfo structures in output buffer.
